"a.喧闹的；猛烈的 【英】 adj.喧闹的(noisy and unruly) 【考】 反义词：quiet(安静 的) 【记】 boister(喧闹)+ous→ 喧闹的 【同】 近形词：bolster(支 持); preposterous(荒谬的) 【例】 The friends played a boisterous game of football. adj. (风、海水、行动、言词等)狂暴的, 汹涌的; (人或其行动兴高采烈的)喧闹的, 吵吵嚷嚷的 = noisy = unruly = blatant 【根】boister(粗鲁的, 粗暴的, 喧闹), ous多－喧闹的, 狂暴的 【记】boi = boil(v 沸腾)－水沸腾的感觉－喧闹的, 狂暴的 【参】preposterous(adj 荒谬的) 【反】quiet(adj 安静的) 【记】汹涌, 猛烈, 热情高涨，喧闹的 boil 水沸腾般； boisterous (adj.)  late 15c., unexplained alteration of Middle English boistous (c.1300) ""rough, coarse (as of food), clumsy, violent,"" of unknown origin, perhaps from Anglo-French bustous ""rough (road),"" which is perhaps from Old French boisteos ""curved, lame; uneven, rough"" (Modern French boiteux), itself of obscure origin. Another guess traces it via Celtic to Latin bestia. Used of persons from 1560s. Related: Boisterously; boisterousness."
